yet another way for this summit
Good in winter when snow is solid

The way up to summit is a bit hard (average 33% sloope); its only 3.3km walk. The way down is easier but you need a good feeling to found your way as there is no foot-path. You can park at the Villard, or at the Chastel. As usual very warm in summer, with some sheep on your way.
